# JVM arguments to add to C:\Program Files\DBeaver\dbeaver.ini, AFTER the line `-vmargs`.
# Edit dbeaver.ini as Administrator. One argument per line. No surrounding quotes.
# Restart DBeaver after editing.

-Djava.security.krb5.conf=C:\ProgramData\MIT\Kerberos5\krb5.ini
-Djavax.security.auth.useSubjectCredsOnly=false
-Dsun.security.krb5.debug=false
-Dsun.security.jgss.debug=false

# Flip the two debug flags to `true` while troubleshooting, then back to `false`.
# When debug is on, launch DBeaver from a PowerShell window to see GSS/Kerberos trace:
#   & "C:\Program Files\DBeaver\dbeaver.exe"
#
# Note: KRB5CCNAME is NOT a -D property. Set it as a User-scope environment variable
# (see docs/06-windows-lsa-and-ccache.md, section 2b).
